{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Thouless-Anderson-Palmer mean field approximation\n",
    "\n",
    "We show in the following the performance of Thouless-Anderson-Palmer mean field approximation (TAP) in inferring couplings $W_{ij}$. Similar to nMF, TAP works well only in the regimes of large sample sizes and small coupling variance.\n",
    "\n",
    "Similary, we import the packages to the notebook:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import simulate\n",
    "import inference\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We first consider a system of $N = 100$ variables, coupling variance parameter $g = 2.0$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# parameter setting:\n",
    "n = 100    # number of variables\n",
    "g = 2.0    # coupling variance\n",
    "w0 = np.random.normal(0.0,g/np.sqrt(n),size=(n,n))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Data length $L=2000$ is used as the first test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "l = 2000\n",
    "s = simulate.generate_data(w0,l)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We apply TAP method to recover the coupling matrix from variable configurations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "w = inference.tap(s)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We plot the heat map of predicted coupling matrix `W` and compare with the actual couplings `W0`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 792x230.4 with 5 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(11,3.2))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,0))\n",
    "plt.title('actual coupling matrix')\n",
    "plt.imshow(w0,cmap='rainbow',origin='lower')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('j')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('i')\n",
    "plt.clim(-0.5,0.5)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(fraction=0.045, pad=0.05,ticks=[-0.5,0,0.5])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,1))\n",
    "plt.title('predicted coupling matrix')\n",
    "plt.imshow(w,cmap='rainbow',origin='lower')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('j')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('i')\n",
    "plt.clim(-0.5,0.5)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(fraction=0.045, pad=0.05,ticks=[-0.5,0,0.5])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,2))\n",
    "plt.title('predicted couplings vs. actual couplings')\n",
    "plt.plot([-1,1],[-1,1],'r--')\n",
    "plt.scatter(w0,w)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('$w0$')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('$w$')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(h_pad=1, w_pad=1.5)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The mean square error between actual couplings and predicted couplings is calculated:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "('MSE:', 0.009013103811623076)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "MSE = np.mean((w-w0)**2)\n",
    "print('MSE:',MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, assumming that we have large number of samples, $L=100000$ for instance."

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 792x230.4 with 5 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [

    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,0))\n",

    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,1))\n",
    "plt.title('predicted coupling matrix')\n",
    "plt.imshow(w,cmap='rainbow',origin='lower')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('j')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('i')\n",
    "plt.clim(-0.5,0.5)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(fraction=0.045, pad=0.05,ticks=[-0.5,0,0.5])\n",

    "plt.subplot2grid((1,3),(0,2))\n",

    "plt.plot([-1,1],[-1,1],'r--')\n",

    "plt.xlabel('$w0$')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('$w$')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(h_pad=1, w_pad=1.5)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
